type: web_research
title: Claude Code Router (CCR) OAuth Passthrough Investigation - January 2026
source: "https://github.com/musistudio/claude-code-router, https://code.claude.com/docs/en/llm-gateway, https://github.com/nsxdavid/anthropic-max-router, https://github.com/BerriAI/litellm/issues/19618"
key_insights[7]: CCR's Anthropic transformer preserves original request/response parameters but replaces OAuth tokens with configured API keys from config.json,CCR uses ANTHROPIC_AUTH_TOKEN environment variable which gets sent as Authorization header - this is NOT the same as forwarding Claude Max OAuth tokens,"Anthropic deployed OAuth restrictions on January 9, 2026 blocking third-party tools from using Claude Pro/Max subscription tokens outside official Claude Code CLI","The restriction is content-based validation: checks for specific system prompt 'You are Claude Code, Anthropic's official CLI for Claude' as first element in system array","LiteLLM has incomplete OAuth implementation - strips Authorization headers in clean_headers() and only forwards x-* headers, not Bearer tokens","anthropic-max-router implements OAuth PKCE flow directly and includes bearer token passthrough, but predates Jan 2026 restrictions (verified working Nov 2025)","ccproxy has forward_oauth hook that extracts tokens from ~/.claude/.credentials.json for passthrough, but no confirmation it works post-Jan 2026"
findings[6]: CCR does NOT passthrough Claude Max OAuth tokens - it replaces them with configured API keys per provider,"Official Claude Code documentation shows ANTHROPIC_BASE_URL proxy setup but confirms Authorization headers are used for gateway auth, not necessarily forwarded",Anthropic's restriction validates request body content (system prompt) not just headers or network signatures,"Multiple proxy projects (LiteLLM, Letta) explicitly strip Authorization headers preventing OAuth passthrough",anthropic-max-router claims bearer token passthrough works but status unknown after Jan 9 2026 crackdown,No confirmed community reports of Claude Max OAuth working through CCR or similar proxies after Jan 2026 restrictions
techniques:
  "OAuth PKCE Flow": Used by anthropic-max-router to obtain tokens from claude.ai/oauth/authorize
  "Content-based Validation": Anthropic checks system prompt 'You are Claude Code...' as first element
  "Bearer Token Passthrough": "Forwarding Authorization: Bearer headers unchanged through proxy"
  "Header Stripping": "Most proxies (LiteLLM, Letta) strip Authorization headers preventing OAuth"
  "Environment Token Injection": CCR sets ANTHROPIC_AUTH_TOKEN but this replaces OAuth tokens with API keys
recommendations[5]: Do NOT rely on CCR for Claude Max OAuth passthrough - it replaces tokens with API keys,anthropic-max-router is the most promising candidate but needs testing to verify if it still works post-Jan 2026,"If using proxies, they must: (1) forward Authorization: Bearer headers unchanged, (2) inject system prompt 'You are Claude Code...', (3) include anthropic-beta: oauth-2025-04-20 header","Consider anthropic-max-router approach: implement OAuth PKCE flow directly + correct system prompt injection","Alternative: accept Claude Max can't be proxied and use regular API keys with routing for cost optimization"
